ied linguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aDeafxLegal status, laws, etc. 0aSign languagexLaw and legislation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Alphabets & Writing Systems.2bisacsh  aDeaf Activisim.  aDeaf Culture.  aDeaf Rights.  aDeaf.  aLanguage policy.  aLegal Rights.  aMinority languages.  aSign Language.  aSign language rights.1 aAzzopardi-Alexander, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorg, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosch-Baliarda, Marta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosco Conama, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByun, Seung-Il, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallus, Dorianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallus, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCantin, Yann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCokart, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Meulder, Maartje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Meulder, Maartje, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDotter, Franz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEncrevé, Florence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeraci, Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Maribel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Menchu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaesenne, Thierry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHong, Sung-Eun, econt